[
    {
        "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": " Hey there, I'm Diana.",
        "start": 2.76,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "And you're watching\n\"Physics Girl.\"",
        "start": 4.36,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Last week, NASA made\nthis big announcement",
        "start": 5.86,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "about a new planetary\nsystem we found",
        "start": 8.35,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "with a star called Trappist-1,\nseven earth-like planets.",
        "start": 10.33,
        "duration": 4.583
    },
    {
        "text": "[SINGS ANGELICALLY]",
        "start": 14.913,
        "duration": 1.197
    },
    {
        "text": "It's 39 light years away.",
        "start": 16.11,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "But that would still take\nsome millions of years",
        "start": 18.04,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "to get to, with\ncurrent technology.",
        "start": 20.23,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "So tough luck on visiting it.",
        "start": 21.79,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "But there are still some crazy\nthings about this system.",
        "start": 24.1,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "The planets are all way\ncloser to their star",
        "start": 26.65,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "than even Mercury is to our sun.",
        "start": 28.99,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "There's a possibility some\nof them are habitable.",
        "start": 31.24,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "And the telescope that\nfound them and the star",
        "start": 34.04,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "are both named after\na Belgian beer.",
        "start": 36.01,
        "duration": 2.286
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 38.296,
        "duration": 1.024
    },
    {
        "text": "Good stuff.",
        "start": 39.32,
        "duration": 0.64
    },
    {
        "text": "I got to interview\none of the scientists",
        "start": 39.96,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "on the team, who was also\nmy first freshman physics",
        "start": 41.74,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "professor at MIT.",
        "start": 44.29,
        "duration": 0.996
    },
    {
        "text": "And I had a quick Skype\nchat with another scientist",
        "start": 45.286,
        "duration": 2.124
    },
    {
        "text": "on the team.",
        "start": 47.41,
        "duration": 0.51
    },
    {
        "text": "I asked them all\nabout this discovery.",
        "start": 47.92,
        "duration": 3.43
    },
    {
        "text": "Is it-- is it exciting?",
        "start": 51.35,
        "duration": 1.07
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't know.",
        "start": 52.42,
        "duration": 0.84
    },
    {
        "text": "Is it--",
        "start": 53.26,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": " Well, it's sort of OK.",
        "start": 54.43,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "No, it's super exciting!",
        "start": 55.68,
        "duration": 1.09
    },
    {
        "text": "Of course it's exciting.",
        "start": 56.77,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "It's an amazing,\nlike, discovery.",
        "start": 57.77,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": " Trappist was\ntrending on Facebook.",
        "start": 59.35,
        "duration": 2.045
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah, yeah.",
        "start": 61.395,
        "duration": 0.949
    },
    {
        "text": "It was super exciting.",
        "start": 62.344,
        "duration": 0.916
    },
    {
        "text": "I kept getting like, messages\nfrom my friends during the day,",
        "start": 63.26,
        "duration": 2.871
    },
    {
        "text": "being like, oh it\nshowed up here.",
        "start": 66.131,
        "duration": 1.374
    },
    {
        "text": "It showed up here.",
        "start": 67.505,
        "duration": 0.755
    },
    {
        "text": " You know, I would get\nin the car with like,",
        "start": 68.26,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "the Uber driver and like,\nthey'd be-- he'd be like, oh,",
        "start": 69.48,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "what are you doing?",
        "start": 71.78,
        "duration": 0.47
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm like, oh, did you\nhear about these planets?",
        "start": 72.25,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "And they're like, oh yeah,\nthat's the most amazing thing.",
        "start": 73.75,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "I was like, I was one\nof the discoverers.",
        "start": 75.58,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "And they're like, can\nI get your picture?",
        "start": 76.54,
        "duration": 1.708
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 78.248,
        "duration": 0.568
    },
    {
        "text": " You are Uber-driver famous.",
        "start": 78.816,
        "duration": 1.254
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 80.07,
        "duration": 0.75
    },
    {
        "text": " Exactly.",
        "start": 80.82,
        "duration": 0.66
    },
    {
        "text": "Right?",
        "start": 81.48,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Like, once you hit that level.",
        "start": 81.98,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: I know.",
        "start": 83.41,
        "duration": 0.583
    },
    {
        "text": "But the most important question,\nwhat have we discovered?",
        "start": 83.993,
        "duration": 3.002
    },
    {
        "text": " So we found seven earth-sized\nplanets around a nearby star.",
        "start": 86.995,
        "duration": 4.035
    },
    {
        "text": "And the seven planets are\nspaced pretty evenly away",
        "start": 91.03,
        "duration": 4.02
    },
    {
        "text": "from the star.",
        "start": 95.05,
        "duration": 0.63
    },
    {
        "text": "And three of them are kind\nof right in the middle,",
        "start": 95.68,
        "duration": 2.083
    },
    {
        "text": "where we think that\nwater could possibly",
        "start": 97.763,
        "duration": 2.447
    },
    {
        "text": "exist on their surfaces.",
        "start": 100.21,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "So we actually wrote\na paper last year,",
        "start": 101.56,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "reporting the discovery of\nthree planets around the system.",
        "start": 104.56,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 107.06,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " And then in December of\n2015, one of my colleagues",
        "start": 107.56,
        "duration": 4.17
    },
    {
        "text": "got a transit with the very\nlarge telescope in Chile.",
        "start": 111.73,
        "duration": 3.26
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Mhm.",
        "start": 114.99,
        "duration": 0.64
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: And the transit\nwas really bonkers.",
        "start": 115.63,
        "duration": 1.955
    },
    {
        "text": "So usually when\nwe see a transit,",
        "start": 117.585,
        "duration": 1.375
    },
    {
        "text": "we kind of see\nlike, a little dip.",
        "start": 118.96,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "And then it kind of comes\nback up, and it's very normal.",
        "start": 120.01,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Mhm.",
        "start": 121.78,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: This was like this,\nkind of wonky, up and down.",
        "start": 122.279,
        "duration": 3.191
    },
    {
        "text": "And initially, we\njust thought, well,",
        "start": 125.47,
        "duration": 1.744
    },
    {
        "text": "there's something like, just\nwrong with our calibration",
        "start": 127.214,
        "duration": 2.291
    },
    {
        "text": "or data or something like that.",
        "start": 129.505,
        "duration": 1.305
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Yeah, yeah.",
        "start": 130.81,
        "duration": 0.51
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: But one\nof our teammates",
        "start": 131.32,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "kind of realized that--\nis that this was actually",
        "start": 132.85,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "the transit of multiple planets\npassing in front of the star.",
        "start": 134.92,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Mm.",
        "start": 137.14,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: And at the time, we\ndidn't-- hadn't actually found",
        "start": 137.64,
        "duration": 3.052
    },
    {
        "text": "those three planets yet. so--",
        "start": 140.692,
        "duration": 1.208
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Right.",
        "start": 141.9,
        "duration": 0.541
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: So-- so we were\nlike, wow, something is--",
        "start": 142.441,
        "duration": 2.571
    },
    {
        "text": "there's-- there's some-- there's\nother stuff going on here.",
        "start": 145.012,
        "duration": 2.458
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Yeah.",
        "start": 147.47,
        "duration": 0.38
    },
    {
        "text": "One thing that I've\nheard, and I'm like, pfft.",
        "start": 147.85,
        "duration": 1.916
    },
    {
        "text": "But I have heard a lot\nthat people are like,",
        "start": 149.766,
        "duration": 2.444
    },
    {
        "text": "we've discovered so\nmany exoplanets lately.",
        "start": 152.21,
        "duration": 1.795
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: Mhm.",
        "start": 154.005,
        "duration": 0.625
    },
    {
        "text": " Like, what is so exciting\nabout this particular system?",
        "start": 154.63,
        "duration": 2.374
    },
    {
        "text": " So a few things.",
        "start": 157.004,
        "duration": 1.436
    },
    {
        "text": "So obviously, the fact\nthat they're all Earth-size",
        "start": 158.44,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "is very new.",
        "start": 160.63,
        "duration": 0.64
    },
    {
        "text": "Right?",
        "start": 161.27,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "So up to this point,\nmost of the planets",
        "start": 161.77,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "we find, kind from our\nvarious techniques,",
        "start": 163.96,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "have usually been\nbig gas giants.",
        "start": 166.03,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "But of course, we've never\nseen this many planets",
        "start": 167.51,
        "duration": 2.81
    },
    {
        "text": "around another star.",
        "start": 170.32,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "And we've definitely never seen\nthis many Earth-sized planets",
        "start": 171.28,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "around another star.",
        "start": 173.47,
        "duration": 0.833
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, not even\naround our star.",
        "start": 174.303,
        "duration": 1.437
    },
    {
        "text": "Right?",
        "start": 175.74,
        "duration": 0.25
    },
    {
        "text": "We've got four.",
        "start": 175.99,
        "duration": 0.701
    },
    {
        "text": "That's it.",
        "start": 176.691,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "So this is already--\nbeats that to-- to spades.",
        "start": 177.19,
        "duration": 2.347
    },
    {
        "text": "One of the big questions we're\ntrying to ask, all of us,",
        "start": 179.537,
        "duration": 2.333
    },
    {
        "text": "sort of in astronomy, is are\nwe alone in the universe?",
        "start": 181.87,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "Like, how did we get here?",
        "start": 184.57,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "Is life unique to this planet?",
        "start": 185.92,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": " Like, what does it all mean?",
        "start": 187.41,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "And then this is like,\ndoes it mean more?",
        "start": 189.05,
        "duration": 1.895
    },
    {
        "text": " Right.",
        "start": 190.945,
        "duration": 0.635
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, is life elsewhere\nin the universe?",
        "start": 191.58,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "And you know, one\nof the things we",
        "start": 194.02,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "know, in terms of ingredients\nfor life on this planet,",
        "start": 196.27,
        "duration": 2.329
    },
    {
        "text": "is the fact that it\nhas liquid water.",
        "start": 198.599,
        "duration": 1.541
    },
    {
        "text": "Right?",
        "start": 200.14,
        "duration": 0.18
    },
    {
        "text": "Nowhere else in the solar\nsystem, as far as we know,",
        "start": 200.32,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "has liquid water on\nits surface today.",
        "start": 202.52,
        "duration": 2.59
    },
    {
        "text": "We have found lots of planets\nthat are huge planets,",
        "start": 205.11,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Jupiter-sized planets.",
        "start": 207.43,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Those are probably\njust big gas balls",
        "start": 208.43,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "and not great places\nto stand around.",
        "start": 210.01,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "And so that's why the\nsizes are important.",
        "start": 212.5,
        "duration": 2.009
    },
    {
        "text": "And then, of course, the\ndistances are important.",
        "start": 214.509,
        "duration": 2.041
    },
    {
        "text": "Because they tell us\nhow much heat they're",
        "start": 216.55,
        "duration": 1.862
    },
    {
        "text": "getting from their\nstar, and whether they",
        "start": 218.412,
        "duration": 1.708
    },
    {
        "text": "have liquid water on them.",
        "start": 220.12,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: You know, in the same\nway that people study galaxies",
        "start": 221.4,
        "duration": 2.458
    },
    {
        "text": "or stars, planets are these--\nand planetary systems are",
        "start": 223.858,
        "duration": 2.652
    },
    {
        "text": "these very interesting\ndynamical systems.",
        "start": 226.51,
        "duration": 1.839
    },
    {
        "text": "And we want to\nknow, just like we",
        "start": 228.349,
        "duration": 1.374
    },
    {
        "text": "want to know how galaxies form\nand how the universe formed",
        "start": 229.723,
        "duration": 2.057
    },
    {
        "text": "and how stars formed.",
        "start": 231.78,
        "duration": 0.86
    },
    {
        "text": "We want to know\nhow planets form.",
        "start": 232.64,
        "duration": 1.04
    },
    {
        "text": "And you know, we can look at\nall the different types of stars",
        "start": 233.68,
        "duration": 2.73
    },
    {
        "text": "and understand something\nabout their evolution.",
        "start": 236.41,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "And for me, it was\nvery interesting",
        "start": 239.27,
        "duration": 1.739
    },
    {
        "text": "just to think about\nplanetary systems",
        "start": 241.009,
        "duration": 1.541
    },
    {
        "text": "as sort of this new\nclass of object.",
        "start": 242.55,
        "duration": 2.05
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't know how answerable\nthis question is.",
        "start": 244.6,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": " 42.",
        "start": 247.52,
        "duration": 0.54
    },
    {
        "text": "42.",
        "start": 248.06,
        "duration": 0.07
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: There's\nso many questions.",
        "start": 248.13,
        "duration": 0.61
    },
    {
        "text": " 42.",
        "start": 248.74,
        "duration": 0.22
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: 42.",
        "start": 248.96,
        "duration": 0.38
    },
    {
        "text": " 42.",
        "start": 249.34,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 249.84,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Because I want\nto ask about like,",
        "start": 250.63,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "what it would potentially be\nlike, living on these planets.",
        "start": 251.89,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": " Mm.",
        "start": 254.37,
        "duration": 0.44
    },
    {
        "text": " But that's going\nto kind of depend on",
        "start": 254.81,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": "whether they're tidally locked.",
        "start": 256.12,
        "duration": 1.349
    },
    {
        "text": " So the first\nthing I want to do",
        "start": 257.469,
        "duration": 1.711
    },
    {
        "text": "is find out if there\nis an atmosphere.",
        "start": 259.18,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "And we can do that\nbecause when-- so the way",
        "start": 260.93,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "we-- actually, go back.",
        "start": 263.03,
        "duration": 0.65
    },
    {
        "text": "The way we found these\nplanets is that they",
        "start": 263.68,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "pass in front of their star.",
        "start": 265.06,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Mhm.",
        "start": 266.44,
        "duration": 0.72
    },
    {
        "text": " And they block out just that\ntiny, tiny little bit of light.",
        "start": 267.16,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "Here, I've even\ngot a little demo.",
        "start": 269.5,
        "duration": 1.11
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Oh, great.",
        "start": 270.61,
        "duration": 0.708
    },
    {
        "text": " So here's a sparkly\nlittle Trappist-1,",
        "start": 271.318,
        "duration": 2.232
    },
    {
        "text": "blinking in its redness.",
        "start": 273.55,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "And here's one of the\nplanets passing in front.",
        "start": 275.17,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "Watch it carefully.",
        "start": 277.96,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "That was very exciting.",
        "start": 279.43,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "OK.",
        "start": 280.51,
        "duration": 0.28
    },
    {
        "text": "So--",
        "start": 280.79,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 281.29,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "--and it blocks about that\nmuch light, which is about 1%",
        "start": 282.54,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "of the light from Trappist-1.",
        "start": 285.46,
        "duration": 1.211
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Mhm.",
        "start": 286.671,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": " So it's a tiny little signal.",
        "start": 287.17,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "So that's how we\nfind the planet.",
        "start": 288.53,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, some of that light,\nif there is an atmosphere,",
        "start": 290.02,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "also kind of filters\naround the planet.",
        "start": 292.48,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "And through the atmosphere.",
        "start": 295.27,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: So molecules\nin the atmosphere",
        "start": 296.79,
        "duration": 2.02
    },
    {
        "text": "will interact\nslightly differently",
        "start": 298.81,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "with different\ncolors of starlight.",
        "start": 300.4,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "And so if you look\nat the light coming",
        "start": 302.18,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "through the atmosphere, when\nthe planet's in transit,",
        "start": 304.31,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "you can start to\nprobe what molecules",
        "start": 307.1,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "are in the atmosphere.",
        "start": 309.77,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm surprised that\nthis is possible.",
        "start": 310.73,
        "duration": 2.021
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 312.751,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": " Because--",
        "start": 313.25,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
        "start": 313.749,
        "duration": 1.281
    },
    {
        "text": " Why?",
        "start": 315.03,
        "duration": 0.73
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Because--",
        "start": 315.76,
        "duration": 0.666
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
        "start": 316.426,
        "duration": 0.634
    },
    {
        "text": "--you've got so much\nlight coming from the--",
        "start": 317.06,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "from the star.",
        "start": 319.67,
        "duration": 0.9
    },
    {
        "text": "And then the amount\nof light that is going",
        "start": 320.57,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "through the atmosphere is--",
        "start": 323.12,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": " Tiny.",
        "start": 325.31,
        "duration": 0.531
    },
    {
        "text": " Tiny.",
        "start": 325.841,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "Like--",
        "start": 326.34,
        "duration": 0.27
    },
    {
        "text": " Tiny.",
        "start": 326.61,
        "duration": 0.44
    },
    {
        "text": "When I did the planet passing\nin front of the start,",
        "start": 327.05,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "that's a 1% effect.",
        "start": 329.24,
        "duration": 1.289
    },
    {
        "text": "When we measure the light\ngoing through the atmosphere,",
        "start": 330.529,
        "duration": 2.291
    },
    {
        "text": "it's like, a\nparts-per-million measurement.",
        "start": 332.82,
        "duration": 2.12
    },
    {
        "text": "So it's a tiny little signal.",
        "start": 334.94,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": " So the next step is\nreally going to be--",
        "start": 336.62,
        "duration": 1.845
    },
    {
        "text": "be studying the make-up\nof the atmospheres,",
        "start": 338.465,
        "duration": 2.75
    },
    {
        "text": "using the absorption of light\nthrough the atmospheres.",
        "start": 341.215,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": " So that's going to be huge.",
        "start": 343.465,
        "duration": 1.255
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, really,\nprobably can be done",
        "start": 344.72,
        "duration": 1.59
    },
    {
        "text": "with JWST, which--\nthe James Webb",
        "start": 346.31,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Space Telescope, which\nactually hasn't launched yet.",
        "start": 348.47,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: When does that launch?",
        "start": 350.84,
        "duration": 0.81
    },
    {
        "text": "KATHERINE DECK:\nIt'll be next year.",
        "start": 351.65,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't know exactly when.",
        "start": 352.97,
        "duration": 1.093
    },
    {
        "text": " Ugh!",
        "start": 354.063,
        "duration": 0.343
    },
    {
        "text": "KATHERINE DECK: But\nyeah, it's supposed",
        "start": 354.406,
        "duration": 1.144
    },
    {
        "text": "to be next year sometime.",
        "start": 355.55,
        "duration": 0.57
    },
    {
        "text": "So--",
        "start": 356.12,
        "duration": 0.37
    },
    {
        "text": " That's really exciting.",
        "start": 356.49,
        "duration": 0.83
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 357.32,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " What level are we at with our\nknowledge about the composition",
        "start": 357.82,
        "duration": 3.125
    },
    {
        "text": "of these planets yet?",
        "start": 360.945,
        "duration": 0.875
    },
    {
        "text": " We can say that we\nthink that they're",
        "start": 361.82,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": "rocky with some atmosphere,\nor primarily rocky",
        "start": 362.99,
        "duration": 2.179
    },
    {
        "text": "with atmosphere.",
        "start": 365.169,
        "duration": 0.666
    },
    {
        "text": "But we're not at the\npoint where we can say",
        "start": 365.835,
        "duration": 2.435
    },
    {
        "text": "how much atmosphere there is.",
        "start": 368.27,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: So\nthere's two problems.",
        "start": 369.62,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": "One is that there's\nseven planets.",
        "start": 370.53,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": "So that pull is like, whoa,\nwhoa, whoa, back and forth",
        "start": 372.02,
        "duration": 3.07
    },
    {
        "text": "in the crazy way.",
        "start": 375.09,
        "duration": 0.88
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Yeah.",
        "start": 375.97,
        "duration": 0.16
    },
    {
        "text": "So the planets are interacting\nwith each other as well?",
        "start": 376.13,
        "duration": 1.995
    },
    {
        "text": " Yes.",
        "start": 378.125,
        "duration": 0.765
    },
    {
        "text": " In this system, what's\ndifferent is that the planets",
        "start": 378.89,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "are near what's called\nmean-motion resonances.",
        "start": 382.13,
        "duration": 3.072
    },
    {
        "text": "So these are where--\nthese are sort",
        "start": 385.202,
        "duration": 1.458
    },
    {
        "text": "of special orbital locations,\nwhere the period of two planet",
        "start": 386.66,
        "duration": 3.15
    },
    {
        "text": "forms an integer ratio.",
        "start": 389.81,
        "duration": 1.749
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: It's like-- it's\nlike in a car, when",
        "start": 391.559,
        "duration": 1.791
    },
    {
        "text": "the one in front\nof you is you know,",
        "start": 393.35,
        "duration": 1.499
    },
    {
        "text": "maybe blinking twice every\ntime yours blinks once.",
        "start": 394.849,
        "duration": 2.401
    },
    {
        "text": "And-- or you know, they meet\nup every once in a while.",
        "start": 397.25,
        "duration": 2.34
    },
    {
        "text": "So one's going around twice,\nevery time one goes around--",
        "start": 399.59,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "I can't do that.",
        "start": 401.6,
        "duration": 0.735
    },
    {
        "text": "KATHERINE DECK: Yeah.",
        "start": 402.335,
        "duration": 0.595
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah, that's hard, yeah, yeah.",
        "start": 402.93,
        "duration": 1.249
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah.",
        "start": 404.179,
        "duration": 0.761
    },
    {
        "text": "And when you're in\nconfigurations like that,",
        "start": 404.94,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": "you can end up where basically\nthe small gravitational sort",
        "start": 407.09,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "of kicks that the planet\ngive each other, they",
        "start": 410.48,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "end up sort of meeting each\nother at the right time",
        "start": 412.61,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "in their orbit.",
        "start": 414.41,
        "duration": 0.625
    },
    {
        "text": "So that those kicks\nadd up coherently.",
        "start": 415.035,
        "duration": 2.435
    },
    {
        "text": "It'd be like if you're\npushing someone on the swing.",
        "start": 417.47,
        "duration": 2.31
    },
    {
        "text": "Every time the person's back,\nthat's when you push them.",
        "start": 419.78,
        "duration": 3.06
    },
    {
        "text": "So your-- your pushes\nadd up, and the person",
        "start": 422.84,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "starts swinging more and more.",
        "start": 425.06,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": " That does not happen\nin our solar system.",
        "start": 426.31,
        "duration": 2.475
    },
    {
        "text": " It does happen in\nour solar system,",
        "start": 428.785,
        "duration": 1.825
    },
    {
        "text": "with the moons of\nJupiter, right?",
        "start": 430.61,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "So Jupiter's moons are\nvery close together.",
        "start": 432.7,
        "duration": 2.78
    },
    {
        "text": "So what the result\nof that, is that Io",
        "start": 435.48,
        "duration": 5.03
    },
    {
        "text": "is in this funny configuration,\nwhere it gets kind of yanked",
        "start": 440.51,
        "duration": 3.42
    },
    {
        "text": "into a slightly eccentric orbit.",
        "start": 443.93,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "And then Jupiter tries to yank\nit back into a circular orbit.",
        "start": 445.94,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "And Io gets yanked\nback and forth.",
        "start": 448.73,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Yeah.",
        "start": 450.5,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " That yanking\ncauses it to stretch.",
        "start": 451.0,
        "duration": 2.44
    },
    {
        "text": "And that stretching causes\nit to become volcanic.",
        "start": 453.44,
        "duration": 2.699
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: That--",
        "start": 456.139,
        "duration": 0.541
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: It heats\nup from the inside.",
        "start": 456.68,
        "duration": 1.245
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Wow.",
        "start": 457.925,
        "duration": 0.57
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: Yeah.",
        "start": 458.495,
        "duration": 0.855
    },
    {
        "text": "These planets are also in\npretty close residence.",
        "start": 459.35,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "And that's why we\nsee these timing--",
        "start": 461.93,
        "duration": 1.51
    },
    {
        "text": "transit timing variations.",
        "start": 463.44,
        "duration": 1.324
    },
    {
        "text": " Man.",
        "start": 464.764,
        "duration": 0.826
    },
    {
        "text": " Yeah.",
        "start": 465.59,
        "duration": 0.721
    },
    {
        "text": " Planetary systems\nare complicated.",
        "start": 466.311,
        "duration": 1.499
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
        "start": 467.81,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": " How much do we\nknow about, like,",
        "start": 469.1,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "what it would potentially be\nlike to live on these planets?",
        "start": 471.2,
        "duration": 3.528
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 474.728,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " I think this is a question for\nlike, science-fiction writers,",
        "start": 475.228,
        "duration": 2.624
    },
    {
        "text": "they can chew on for\nmany, many years.",
        "start": 477.852,
        "duration": 2.15
    },
    {
        "text": " Or for curious Diana.",
        "start": 480.002,
        "duration": 1.358
    },
    {
        "text": " Or a curious Diana, yes.",
        "start": 481.36,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "So one-- so one factor\nis that they are so close",
        "start": 483.11,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "to their sun, or their\nstar, that they are probably",
        "start": 486.35,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "tidally locked, just like\nthe moon is tidally locked",
        "start": 489.32,
        "duration": 2.18
    },
    {
        "text": "to the Earth.",
        "start": 491.5,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "And so that has a couple of\ninteresting effects, right?",
        "start": 492.8,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "So one is what time is it?",
        "start": 495.72,
        "duration": 2.966
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 498.686,
        "duration": 1.932
    },
    {
        "text": "That's exactly the\nresponse you would",
        "start": 501.584,
        "duration": 1.596
    },
    {
        "text": "have on one of these planets.",
        "start": 503.18,
        "duration": 1.208
    },
    {
        "text": "Because nothing\nwould change, right?",
        "start": 504.388,
        "duration": 1.582
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Right, right.",
        "start": 505.97,
        "duration": 0.12
    },
    {
        "text": " You wouldn't have the\nsun rising and setting.",
        "start": 506.09,
        "duration": 2.37
    },
    {
        "text": "It would just stay there.",
        "start": 508.46,
        "duration": 1.261
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Yeah.",
        "start": 509.721,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": " Right?",
        "start": 510.22,
        "duration": 0.55
    },
    {
        "text": "And if you're on\nthe day side, you",
        "start": 510.77,
        "duration": 1.416
    },
    {
        "text": "wouldn't even see the stars.",
        "start": 512.186,
        "duration": 1.284
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean, there's many\ncycles in our bodies",
        "start": 513.47,
        "duration": 2.459
    },
    {
        "text": "that are based on the\ncycles in the Earth, right?",
        "start": 515.929,
        "duration": 2.101
    },
    {
        "text": "We wake up and we fall\nasleep on cycles that",
        "start": 518.03,
        "duration": 2.389
    },
    {
        "text": "are based on the day and night.",
        "start": 520.419,
        "duration": 1.291
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Right.",
        "start": 521.71,
        "duration": 0.365
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: We have\nmenstrual cycles",
        "start": 522.075,
        "duration": 1.458
    },
    {
        "text": "that are tied to the moon.",
        "start": 523.533,
        "duration": 1.492
    },
    {
        "text": "Maybe there's a moon.",
        "start": 525.025,
        "duration": 0.875
    },
    {
        "text": "So that would be--",
        "start": 525.9,
        "duration": 0.68
    },
    {
        "text": "that would save you.",
        "start": 526.58,
        "duration": 0.61
    },
    {
        "text": "You'd have-- if you\nhave a moon, you",
        "start": 527.19,
        "duration": 0.92
    },
    {
        "text": "kind of know what time it is.",
        "start": 528.11,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Right?",
        "start": 529.43,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, imagine you have a world\nthat has no external triggers,",
        "start": 529.93,
        "duration": 3.25
    },
    {
        "text": "you know, indicators\nof time passing.",
        "start": 533.18,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Yeah.",
        "start": 534.88,
        "duration": 0.76
    },
    {
        "text": " How does life evolve to--",
        "start": 535.64,
        "duration": 2.7
    },
    {
        "text": "to fall into these cycles?",
        "start": 538.34,
        "duration": 1.499
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Right.",
        "start": 539.839,
        "duration": 0.541
    },
    {
        "text": " So actually, one cycle\nthey will see is that--",
        "start": 540.38,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": " You're hurting my brain.",
        "start": 542.81,
        "duration": 0.27
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: I'm sorry.",
        "start": 543.08,
        "duration": 0.874
    },
    {
        "text": "[LAUGHS]",
        "start": 543.954,
        "duration": 0.896
    },
    {
        "text": "So the good thing about\nthese planets being so close",
        "start": 544.85,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "is that you can see them.",
        "start": 546.41,
        "duration": 0.7
    },
    {
        "text": "Right?",
        "start": 547.11,
        "duration": 0.16
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Right.",
        "start": 547.27,
        "duration": 0.541
    },
    {
        "text": " So even if you don't\nhave a moon, you know,",
        "start": 547.811,
        "duration": 2.049
    },
    {
        "text": "if you're standing\non Trappist-1C,",
        "start": 549.86,
        "duration": 3.147
    },
    {
        "text": "you're going to see Trappist-1B\nkind of swing around every day",
        "start": 553.007,
        "duration": 2.583
    },
    {
        "text": "and a half.",
        "start": 555.59,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": "And so that gives you kind\nof a ah, Trappist-1B o'clock.",
        "start": 556.5,
        "duration": 4.41
    },
    {
        "text": "Or it's--",
        "start": 560.91,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Yeah.",
        "start": 561.41,
        "duration": 0.64
    },
    {
        "text": "So these planets are\nreally close together.",
        "start": 562.05,
        "duration": 1.814
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: Yeah.",
        "start": 563.864,
        "duration": 0.666
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah.",
        "start": 564.53,
        "duration": 0.499
    },
    {
        "text": "DIANA: Like the-- I-- they're\nsuper close to their star.",
        "start": 565.029,
        "duration": 2.351
    },
    {
        "text": " Mhm.",
        "start": 567.38,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "In fact, if you compare\nthe size of this system",
        "start": 567.88,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "to the size of Jupiter\nand its moons--",
        "start": 570.41,
        "duration": 2.225
    },
    {
        "text": "which we've talked\nabout before--",
        "start": 572.635,
        "duration": 1.375
    },
    {
        "text": "that's actually pretty close.",
        "start": 574.01,
        "duration": 1.542
    },
    {
        "text": " You've kind of talked\nabout this already,",
        "start": 575.552,
        "duration": 1.263
    },
    {
        "text": "like what we're-- what\nwe're looking for next.",
        "start": 576.815,
        "duration": 1.916
    },
    {
        "text": "So we're-- we're looking\nfor an atmosphere,",
        "start": 578.731,
        "duration": 2.534
    },
    {
        "text": "composition of the atmosphere.",
        "start": 581.265,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "BURGASSER: Yeah.",
        "start": 582.515,
        "duration": 0.405
    },
    {
        "text": " You can think about\nit as sort of a process",
        "start": 582.92,
        "duration": 1.875
    },
    {
        "text": "of characterization, where from\nthe transits, we find planets.",
        "start": 584.795,
        "duration": 3.195
    },
    {
        "text": "We know what their\nperiods are, and we",
        "start": 587.99,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "learned about how big they are.",
        "start": 589.97,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "More transits are going\nto help us measure masses.",
        "start": 591.47,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "So then we get an idea of--\nrough idea of composition,",
        "start": 593.99,
        "duration": 2.43
    },
    {
        "text": "if they're rocky or not.",
        "start": 596.42,
        "duration": 1.711
    },
    {
        "text": "And then, ultimately,\nwe know we want",
        "start": 598.131,
        "duration": 1.541
    },
    {
        "text": "to say OK, what are the\natmospheres made out of?",
        "start": 599.672,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "And that's still to come.",
        "start": 601.672,
        "duration": 1.278
    },
    {
        "text": " We're now starting\nthe SPECULOOS survey.",
        "start": 602.95,
        "duration": 2.83
    },
    {
        "text": " Mhm.",
        "start": 605.78,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": " We chose about 500\nvery low-mass stars,",
        "start": 606.28,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "all within the\nvicinity of the sun.",
        "start": 609.67,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "And what we're going\nto do, in this survey,",
        "start": 612.25,
        "duration": 1.83
    },
    {
        "text": "is actually image\nall of them with--",
        "start": 614.08,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "and do the same\nkind of measurements",
        "start": 616.03,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "for every one of these stars.",
        "start": 617.53,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "And the goal is to actually\nanswer the question,",
        "start": 618.91,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "is this a unique system?",
        "start": 621.49,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Or is this actually\nquite common?",
